    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-dark mb-4">How to Write A Capstone Assignment from A professional Point of View.</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Writing a capstone is a tough task yet very interesting. Students find it hard to come up with a professional, but this guide will help you write a perfect capstone. Follow these steps in writing your assignment.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">Step1: Formulate a Topic</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">At this point, you need to think about the topic that your assignment will cover. It will help if you reflect on your notes come up with the ideas from your previous classes.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">It is best to formulate a topic that interests you and manageable; this will help you write a flawless assignment. You can consult your colleagues or faculty members who have handled a capstone assignment before.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Think about situations where your in-depth knowledge on the course of study can be applied, and pick a topic that you can relate to in your daily life. Your assignment should intensify the knowledge and skills you obtained during the study relating it to the workspace.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">Step 2: Formulate a Capstone Project Proposal</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">It is important to note you need to formulate and submit a proposal to the examiner or tutor. A Paper of 200 words or more will perfectly fix a proposal in a normal situation. Your capstone proposal should do the following:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li class="text-gray-700">Talk about the topic that you have chosen and why you have settled on a particular topic.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">It will help if you emphasize the scope of data available while highlighting the sources of data collection.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">It should talk about your experience and background on a specific topic.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">It should list the basic workplace and human subject authorization.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">It should tell about the planned research stating the methods you planing to use while analyzing the processes.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">You need to set the objectives of your assignment.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">It is advisable to prepare a literature review and state the methods you plan to use if your assignment dictates that you write a broader capstone. It's significant to include everything that will make your assignment attract the examiner; a boring proposal will lead to rejection of the task.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Step 3: Collect Critical Data</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Data collection starts with identifying the sources of information by searching for the information you are going to use in your writing. Reviewing your notes and the sourcebook allows you to get relevant literature to help you in doing your assignment.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">You can record critical information by creating a folder on your computer and state all references recording helpful links. It will be helpful to outline your data in several files, naming them properly adding tags to help you get the data when presenting your points and ideas. You need to highlight the key summaries associated with your topic of discussion. Categorize your summaries to make it easy for you to present your points.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Step 4:</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Once you have all the important information, you now need to outline your work; the format of every capstone assignment differs. Still, it's important to use a clear structure to enable you to split up your ideas, concentrating on each point logically. A typical capstone of consist of the following:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li class="text-gray-700">Title page.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">Introduction.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">Literature review.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">Methods.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">Results and Discussion.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">Conclusion and Recommendations.</li>
        <li class="text-gray-700">References list.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">Step 5: Formulate a schedule</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Capstone assignments are quite voluminous. It makes sense to take some time and plan your understandings. Creating a program with assignments and deadlines will greatly help you develop a concrete capstone assignment. Perfect your schedule occasionally; this will help you to replace the already completed tasks.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Remember that an assignment can take a short time to complete, while others may need more time to complete than you scheduled. To track the progress, you need to use tracking software on your phone or desktop.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">Step 6: Start the Writing process</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The thesis statement is the basis of your capstone assignment; therefore, you must come up with a solid thesis statement. Your statement should be specific and narrow to help you articulate your work. Kindly note that a broad thesis makes it difficult to cover the critical information.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Capstone can be written from any point you need to remember to write an interesting introduction. You need be to be deep on the topic of study to write an engaging introduction. It is also important to state the primary problem listing the limitations of your research.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The literature review section helps you to summarize your findings and critical days on the topic of study. It will help if you make a comprehensive conclusion accompanying it with a brief analysis of each source of your research.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Be critical of your data collection sources, highlighting the loopholes in the data collection. It is also significant to state your opinions or stands when you are writing your capstone assignment. Kindly remember to write every point in its paragraph and elaborate on each idea before moving to the next point.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Your outline should guide you in your work; you only need to write everything in its right section and ensure you don't mix up your work.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">Step 7: Proofread Your work</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">It is important to go through your work. This will help you to identify the manner omission, grammatical errors, and other mistakes. Proofreading offers you an opportunity to correct these errors and ensure that your text is in order.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Always remember that presenting an assignment that is full of errors might affect your score.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">Step 8: Defend Your Work.</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">A good capstone should be defended. In most cases, this process is usually done before the panel. You must maintain a high-quality presentation as it will impact the examination of the whole assignment.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">At this point, you need to state the significance of the topic, discussing the research process while describing the results of your study. Defense is more of a discussion than a presentation as the panel usually goes through your assignment.  Your defense should be precise, brief, and mast not leave and point or idea hanging.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">You don't have to worry about you find the processes of writing a capstone assignment. In case you are stuck with your task, you can always seek assistance from professionals. The experts will ensure that you score a better grade since they have in-depth knowledge and have lots of expertise.</p>
